       . . . Tym/COMM 4.0 RELEASED AUGUST 6:  MORE FOR THE SAME PRICE . . .
     
     Tym/COMM 4.0 now offers more, but at a price that keeps this product
     competitive with CrossTalk and SmartModem.
     
     New features include...
     
     X.PC, an advanced async communications protocol that enables users to
     connect to up to 15 different hosts or network services
     TYMGEN, a simple menu-driven means to set parameters (a breeze for
     novice users)
     SNAPSHOT, a feature that "takes a picture" of scrolling data
     REPLAY, the feature that displays that picture
     
     Enhancements for the novice and the experienced Tym/COMM user:  improved
     menus, monitor color control, and 20 new procedure statements
     
     Tym/COMM's excellent support continues through the Customer Service
     Center 800 number and with a revised user's guide that documents the new
     features.
     
     All this for the competitive price of $295.  However, the other guys
     don't offer site licensing.  (Yet!)  According to product manager Rose
     Hayden, corporations want good discounts, and site licenses are an
     effective way to offer discounts.
     
     New data sheets accompanied the July NEWSFLASH.  Demo diskettes are
     available.  To learn more about the new features or to obtain a demo
     diskette, contact Rose Hayden at ACS.R/HAYDEN.
     
     
              . . . ONTYME VERSION 22:  JUST AROUND THE CORNER . . .
     
     The release of OnTyme Version 22 is scheduled for mid-August, 1986.  The
     new features are highlighted below:
     
     Pathway--enables users to access any computer on the TYMNET network
     XMODEM Protocol--provides error-free file transfer
     X.ONTYME--increases throughput, efficiency, and saves money
     The Reply command--sends the contents of the workspace to the original
     recipients of the message
     Subject line--the text supplied by the sender appears in the message
     header and all the message lists (in, out, old, long, short, etc.)
     
     For a more detailed description of Pathway, XMODEM, and X.ONTYME, please
     see the enclosed data sheet.
     
     
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
